Package: sumvar
Title: Summarise Continuous and Categorical Variables, Check for Duplicates and Missing Data
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Alexander", "Stockdale", , "a.stockdale@liverpool.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: sumvar is a collection of functions useful for summarising variables.
  For continuous variables, the distribution of a single variable use dist_one()
  To explore a continuous variable stratified by a grouping variable use dist_sum()
  For a single categorical variable use tab1(), and a twoway table from two categorical variables- tab().  
  dist_sum() and tab() include options for hypothesis tests.  
  Explore duplicates with dup()) and missing values with miss().
